page.title: 01BARNSBURY ESTATE IN WOKING
page.content: Our estate has three main roads, which are Ash Road, Laburnum Road and Hawthorne Road. It was built 25-30 years ago. It has 2 schools Barnsbury first and middle schools. It has 400-500 houses. It has also four blocks of flats. It has four shops, a Greengrocer, Newsagent, Butcher and a Mace store. It has also one farm which is made up of mostly goats. We have one river which is called 'Hoestream'. The estate has eight different types of houses and also eight greens, and also we have five playing greens, and we have six parking facilities on our estate where some of us live. Also on our estate we have a large wood and marshland area.
